how long should i keep my baby without nourishment for the last two weeks i have been trying get my baby months old to sleep through the night but he stills waking up between am i have been told that i need to let him cry himself out to sleep but since his last nourishment was at pm i'm not sure if he can endure any longer without food does anyone know how long a months old baby should endure without nourishment thnx what i personally did was water down his feed gradually so that his stomach got used to not being fed so early if you are using formula you can easily water it down if you are bf it may be a bit harder unless you are pumping make sure his last feed in the evening is a big one are you also feeding him solids if so then give him a bottle then solids at night good stodge food which lasts longer in his tummy potatoes pastas for example try to not give him fill in food too close to his last meal my son was sleeping throughout the night min of hrs from around months i just had to ensure he was well fed at night he was a hungry little monkey when he woke too on the other hand if it is a comfort thing then it is a bit harder you will need to let him cry a little but not too much you know your baby and will know when enough is enough for him then try comfort him without actually picking him up and leave as quick as you feel is possible if you think he is hungry and he is waking at those times give him a watered down bottle to feed himself with in his bed then leave the room good luck Breastfeeding Mattress Dog training EastEnders Care Bears Fasting Sea-Monkey Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Breakfast The Amber Spyglass Sin City Sleep Kitchen Shark Cuisine of Denmark Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Fertility awareness Baby bottle Infant The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Hamster Social rule Stomach cancer Knots Landing John the Baptist Hell's Kitchen (television) Characters in the Smurfs Shaggy dog story Adjustable gastric band Night (book) Jam (TV se